EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

We are entering the era of Prompted Personalized Software (PPS) â€” where businesses stop adapting to software and software adapts to them. Business OS is the first platform built entirely around this principle for non-technical entrepreneurs. It is a token-based SaaS platform that empowers any business owner to build, deploy, and manage their entire operation from a single, unified dashboard â€” through natural language prompts, with zero coding required. The platform replaces 6â€“12 month implementation cycles and fragmented tooling with one elegant foundation powered by a prepaid token economy.

The Core Idea

You build custom ecommerce apps for clients. Clients pay for tokens to run those apps. Everything is managed in one place. No per-seat pricing, no surprise invoices â€” just simple, transparent usage-based billing.

Problem | Ecommerce businesses juggle 5â€“10 disconnected tools: store builders, order managers, analytics dashboards, email tools, inventory systems. It's expensive, fragmented, and inefficient.

Solution | A unified platform where the founder builds tailored apps for each client, and clients manage everything through one dashboard â€” paying only for the tokens their apps consume.

Revenue Model | Token packs sold upfront. Recurring token subscriptions. Optional app-build service fees. White-label licensing for agencies.

Target Market | Non-technical business owners across all revenue stages â€” restaurateurs, service providers, online sellers, coaches, consultants, and retailers â€” who are building or scaling an online presence and need a complete operational platform without an engineering team.

BUSINESS MODEL

How It Works

The platform operates on three distinct layers that work together to create a seamless experience for both the founder (you) and the client.

Layer | Description | Owner
1. App Building | You build custom apps tailored to each client's ecommerce needs using your platform's internal tooling. | 
2. Dashboard Access | Clients get access to a unified dashboard where all their apps live and can be managed in one place. | 
3. Token Consumption | Every action within the apps (syncing orders, generating reports, sending notifications, etc.) consumes tokens from the client's balance. | 

Revenue Streams

The business generates revenue through four complementary channels:

Revenue Stream | Description | Pricing Model
Token Packs (Pay-as-you-go) | Clients purchase token bundles upfront and consume them at their own pace across all their apps. | $29 / 5,000 tokens$79 / 15,000 tokens$199 / 50,000 tokens
Token Subscriptions | Monthly auto-renewing token plans with a discount vs one-time packs. Ensures predictable recurring revenue. | $49/mo â€” 10,000 tokens$129/mo â€” 30,000 tokens$299/mo â€” 80,000 tokens
App Build Fees | One-time service fee to build and deploy a custom app for a client within the platform. | $500â€“$2,500 per app
White-Label Licensing | Agencies or resellers can license the platform under their own brand to serve their own clients. | $299â€“$999/month

Token Economy Design

The token system is the heartbeat of the platform. It must be intuitive, transparent, and valuable to the client.

Feature | Details
What costs tokens? | Order sync, product updates, automated reports, notification sends, API calls, AI features
What's free? | Dashboard login, viewing data, manual edits, support chat
Token rollover? | Unused tokens roll over for 90 days (subscription) or 12 months (one-time pack)
Token transparency | Clients see a real-time token usage meter and breakdown per app in their dashboard
Low balance alerts | Automatic email/SMS alert at 20% balance remaining â€” with 1-click top-up
Bonus tokens | 10% bonus tokens for referrals, annual plans, or high-volume usage milestones

PLATFORM & PRODUCT

Core Platform Features

The platform has two interfaces: the Client Dashboard (what clients see) and the Founder Console (what you use to build and manage everything).

Client Dashboard

Unified view of all apps, products, and orders in one place

Real-time token balance meter with usage breakdown per app

Order management: view, filter, update, and fulfill orders

Product catalog management: edit listings, inventory, pricing

Analytics: sales trends, top products, customer insights

Notification center: track app activity and platform announcements

One-click token top-up and subscription management

Founder Console (Admin)

App builder: create, configure, and deploy client apps

Client manager: onboard clients, assign apps, set token costs per action

Token ledger: view all token transactions across all clients

Revenue dashboard: MRR, churn, token velocity, top clients

White-label settings: configure branding for agency clients

Support system: ticket management and live chat

App Types You Can Build

