Key Risks & Mitigations

Risk | Mitigation
Client churns after free trial | Ensure strong onboarding, fast value delivery, and check-in calls in first 30 days
Token pricing confuses clients | Always show token equivalent in dollar value. Provide clear usage estimators.
Building apps takes too much time | Templatize common app types. Standardize components. Hire a developer at 20+ clients.
Competitor copies the model | Build strong client relationships. Network effects and switching costs protect you.
Technical debt grows fast | Invest in clean architecture from day one. Use proven frameworks (Next.js, Supabase).

VISION & LONG-TERM OPPORTUNITY

We are building in the most significant moment of software industry disruption since the cloud. Traditional SaaS valuations are collapsing because the market is pricing in the obsolescence of pre-built, rigid software. The winners of the next decade will not sell feature sets â€” they will sell foundations and the capabilities that let customers build their own software. Business OS is that foundation.

Business OS sits at the intersection of three compounding moats: a data moat (every prompt makes the AI smarter), a switching cost moat (clients build their entire operation on the platform), and a network moat (similar-industry clients make the platform better for each other). Unlike traditional SaaS whose value is static, Business OS grows exponentially more valuable with every client added.

