ğŸ’¡  Suggested Future IntegrationAzure (Microsoft cloud) as a third cloud option â€” many enterprise and Latin American companies use Azure. Also Cloudflare for CDN and DNS management, and Vercel/Netlify for frontend-only deployments.

ğŸ¤–  MODULE 2 â€” Prompt Studio (Prompt-to-Product)Build, improve, and deploy features just by describing what you want.

This is the core differentiator of the platform. Clients describe what they want to build or change in plain language, and the AI generates the code, applies it to their repository, and deploys it â€” all with token consumption tracked transparently.

Feature | Description
Prompt Interface | A clean chat-like interface where clients type what they want to create or improve. Example: 'Add a product filter by category and price range to my store homepage.'
AI Code Generation | The platform reads the client's existing codebase from GitHub, understands the architecture, and generates code that fits seamlessly into their project.
One-Click Deploy | After generating a change, the client previews a before/after diff in plain language (not raw code), then clicks 'Deploy' to push to their cloud environment.
Module Library | Pre-built modules clients can activate with a prompt: product catalog, checkout flow, loyalty points, discount engine, customer portal, and more.
Version History | Every prompt-generated change is saved as a versioned snapshot. Clients can roll back to any previous version with one click.
Staging Preview | Before deploying to production, clients can preview changes on a staging URL to make sure everything looks right.
Prompt History & Favorites | All past prompts are saved. Clients can re-run, modify, or save favorite prompts as templates for repeated use.
AI Suggestions | Proactive suggestions from the AI: 'Your checkout page has a high drop-off rate. Want me to simplify the form?' â€” powered by analytics data.

